parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbag to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of serious injury or death to the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact meeting the deployment threshold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel spongy or go to the floor, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
extended stopping distances
loss of control when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheating can cause the brake system to malfunction, leading to a loss of brake effectiveness and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The exterior temperature gauge reaches the red line
the brake pedal becomes very spongy
loss of control when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to speed out of control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the engine does not decelerate after releasing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates to high speed without warning
the driver must apply the brakes to avoid high speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control malfunction can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control disengages while driving
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates without input from the driver
the cruise control system does not function as intended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weakness in the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to bottom out, leading to a loss of control, uneven tire wear, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear suspension bottoms out when there are passengers in the rear seat
the vehicle sags or leans to one side
the vehicle makes squeaking or creaking noises when driving over bumps
the ride is rough and uncomfortable.
